const DEF_GENERAL_RULES='- Use the exact structure below in order.\n- If information is missing, write "Not provided"\n- Professional medical English. Concise but accurate.\n- Return ONLY clean HTML: <h2> for section titles, <p> for content, <strong> for labels. No code blocks.\n- Use narrative prose style.';
const DEF_GENERAL_RULES_ADM='INPUT: Convert all input to clean professional clinical English. Silently translate Spanish — never comment on it. Act immediately with available data — do not ask for clarification first. If a data point is missing, use the section default phrase and continue.\n\nSTYLE: Attending-level clinical English at all times. Narrative prose for HPI — bullets only for PMH, medications, assessments, and plan. Always compare lab values to prior when available. Never use informal language, filler phrases, or hedging. Do not add disclaimers, explanations, or meta-commentary. Do not mention that you translated or corrected the input.\n\nOUTPUT: Return ONLY clean HTML: <h2> for section titles, <p> for content, <strong> for labels. No code blocks.\n\nAFTER THE NOTE: Close with one brief line offering the next step. Use one or two of these emojis at end of message only, never mid-sentence: 🩺 📋 ✅ ✨';
